Pardon me; I know very well what I am about; 
(ſinging and dancing)—The head
upright:— (ſinging and dancing) The body thrown gracefully forward.

Why, you naſty, good for nothing, falſe-hearted creature,
you ought to be aſhamed of yourſelf, ſo you ought: I do love you, then;
I own I do; 
[Burſts out a crying] and if you had not treated
me ſo, I would ſeen him further with all his fine promiſes; but now I'll
go and keep my coach out of ſpight.
